casebody.data:
Attorney Grievance Commission of Maryland, Petitioner
v.
Reid Donalan Henderson, Respondent Misc. Docket AG No. 32, Sept. Term, 2016 Court of Appeals of Maryland. September 16, 2016

ORDER

Upon consideration of the Joint Petition for Disbarment by Consent filed herein pursuant to Maryland Rule 19-736, in which Respondent admits he committed professional misconduct in violation of Rules 1.3, 1.4(a) and (b), and 1.16(a)(2) and (d) of the former Maryland Lawyers' Rules of Professional Conduct, it is this 16th day September , 2016,

ORDERED, that Respondent, Reid Donalan Henderson, be and he is hereby disbarred from the practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall remove the name of Reid Donalan Henderson from the register of attorneys in the Court and certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund of the Bar of Maryland and all clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State in accordance with Maryland Rule 19-742.
